3246	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.isIso_unitToPushforwardObjUnit_of_isIso'}
3247	  \textit{Project-bespoke auxiliary (general continuous-functor fact).}
3248	  Let \(Fu : C \to D\) be a continuous functor of sites and \(\psi : Fu^{*}S \to R\) (equivalently a
3249	  comparison of sheaves of rings) with \(\psi\) an isomorphism. Then the canonical unit comparison
3250	  \(\mathrm{unitToPushforwardObjUnit}\,\psi : \mathbf{1}_S \to (\mathrm{pushforward}\,\psi).\mathrm{obj}\,
3251	  \mathbf{1}_R\) is an isomorphism.
3252	\end{lemma}
3253	\begin{proof}
3254	  Reflecting through the forgetful passage to presheaves, the component of the unit comparison over each
3255	  object \(V\) is the functor-image of \(\psi.\mathrm{app}\,V\); since \(\psi\) is an isomorphism each
3256	  such component is, hence so is the unit comparison. (This is the \(\mathrm{IsIso}\,\psi\)-driven
3257	  criterion, in place of Mathlib's finality-hypothesis form.)
3258	\end{proof}
